        "title": "Shoulder Arthroplasty Indications",
        "definition": "Osteoarthritis, inflammatory arthritis, osteonecrosis, and fracture indications for anatomic versus reverse.",
        "summary": "Intact rotator cuff favors anatomic TSA; cuff deficiency favors reverse."
